news.title: Nagpur: NIT, NMRDA hold Lokshahi Din to resolve citizens’ issues
news.para: The general manager of NIT, Avinash Katade, interacted with the citizens. The majority of the issues were related to layout development under NIT and NMRDA, regularisation, and lease-related.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to introduce Aadhaar-based authentication for property registration
news.para: It involves submitting the Aadhaar number along with demographic or biometric information to the Unique Identification Authority of India's (UIDAI) Central Identities Data Repository (CIDR).

news.title: Government gives Rs 38 crore to 1.1 lakh construction workers in Hassan
news.para: Labour minister Santosh Lad advised the labour department to work actively and directed them to carefully verify before distributing benefits to beneficiaries.

news.title: Chalet Hotels to acquire Westin Resort & Spa Rishikesh at enterprise value of Rs 530 crore
news.para: The company has received the approval of the board of directors for the acquisition, Chalet Hotels Ltd (CHL) said in a statement.

news.title: Contractors will take legal action for non-payment of government dues: BAI
news.para: BAI, MSCA, and the Hot Mix Association, among others, jointly announced on Monday to intensify the protest by stopping work on govt contracts at a joint meeting.

news.title: Maharashtra: Up to 10,000 housing societies await single-window system for clearances
news.para: The state housing department in a GR issued on Sept 13, 2019 had proposed for a single-window system for issuing clearances to allow self-redevelopment of 30-year-old and above properties.

news.title: Private firm to assess value of ‘unsafe’ Chintels Paradiso flats in Gurgaon
news.para: Audits at the Sector 109 society began after a vertical collapse of five floors at Tower D killed two women in Feb 2022. Soon after the incident, the district administration brought in IIT experts to assess the structural safety of residential towers at the apartment complex.

news.title: Haryana-RERA asks builder to refund Rs 6 lakh to buyer
news.para: The buyer, Bharat and Poonam Gupta, had booked a 2BHK flat in Mahira Homes in April 2019 for up-front amount of Rs 1.15 lakh.

news.title: Kalpataru inks 7.5-acre Mumbai redevelopment deals with Rs 2,000 crore revenue
news.para: These projects involve total development of over 1.5 million sq ft with revenue potential of over Rs 2,000 crore. The company is expected to execute both these projects in 42 months from the commencement of construction work, as per the agreements reviewed by ET.

news.title: Suraksha Group-controlled Jaypee Infra gets RERA registration revalidation for seven stalled projects
news.para: In June last year, Mumbai-based Suraksha Group took control of Jaypee Infratech Ltd (JIL) by constituting a three-member board. Sudhir V Valia, promoter of Suraksha Group, was appointed as a non-executive director on the JIL board.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso residents demand justice, urge government to intervene
news.para: ​The partial collapse of Tower D on February 10, 2022, claimed the lives of two women and rendered several families homeless. The residents and the builder have been involved in the litigation since then.

news.title: Grasim Industries' profit drops 29% to Rs 1,844.3 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 8.84 per cent to Rs 34,792.85 crore during the quarter under review compared to Rs 31,965.48 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Signatureglobal (India) posts net profit of Rs 29.13 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Signatureglobal (India)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 862.14 crore in Q3 F25 as against Rs 301.75 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Action Construction Equipment's profit grows 26% to Rs 112 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Income increased to Rs 905.28 crore from Rs 776.08 crore in the year-ago quarter, posting a rise of 16.65 per cent. Expenses were at Rs 755.79 crore as against Rs 661.78 crore a year ago.

news.title: Berger Paints to focus on sustainable growth, open to acquisitions: Chairman
news.para: When asked why the company did not bid for Akzo Nobel's paints business which is up for sale in India, Pakistan and Sri Lanka, the Berger Paints chairman told PTI that "Under the current circumstances, it does not align with our strategy. Therefore, we have not placed any bid so far."

news.title: Shriram Properties to jointly develop residential project in Chennai
news.para: The residential project has a saleable area of 3.2 lakh sq ft and will be developed over the next three years. The project is expected to have aggregate revenue potential of approximately Rs 350 - Rs 400 crore.

news.title: Office leasing demand to grow 8-10% in FY26: Crisil
news.para: Grade A office space completions of 52 million sq ft are likely in the current fiscal, followed by 55-58 million sq ft in the next financial year.

news.title: Asian Granito India reports net sales of Rs 360 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Exports for the Q3 FY25 was reported at Rs 79 crore, rise of 22% year-on-year as compared to export of Rs 60 crore in Q3 FY24 mainly on account of quartz export.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal gates installed in two colonies razed in DTCP operation
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia warned that all unauthorised gates erected by Resident Welfare Associations (RWAs) in licensed colonies will be removed.

news.title: Noida authority set to take private help to monitor NCLT cases and land dues
news.para: The Authority has issued a Request for Proposal (RFP) for consultancy services and interested firms can submit their bids by Feb 18, after which the technical evaluation will take place the following day.
